Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan will lock horns with South Africa in the 26th game of the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023 at the MA Chidambaram Stadium, Chennai on October 27 at 2:00 PM IST.
Pakistan have played 5 matches in the series and are currently ranked fifth on the points table, while South Africa have also played 5 matches and are currently ranked second.
The pitch at the MA Chidambaram Stadium, Chennai is a balanced pitch with an average 1st innings score of 221 runs in the last 20 matches.
The temperature will hover around 30°C with 63% humidity and winds at a speed of 4.76 m/s are expected.
The venue is suited for both pacers and spinners alike.
In the 82 matches played between Pakistan and South Africa, the batters of both teams have earned the most fantasy points for their respective teams so far.
